declarations.comments: Requires the input to have a zero-valued fractional component.
declarations.title: fromHugeNum

declarations.comments:
Input must look like a Purescript `Int`.
For example, `fromString "123456789012345" => Just (HugeInt 123456789012345)`.
declarations.title: fromString

declarations.comments:
Creates a HugeNum from a Number.
May lose precision if the argument is too large.
declarations.title: toNumber

declarations.comments:
Create a HugeNum from a String.
Strings should be in the form of a Purescript `Number`. For example,
`fromString "123.456" => Just (HugeNum 123.456)`
declarations.title: fromString

declarations.comments: Limits the number of digits past the decimal.
declarations.title: truncate

declarations.comments: Counts how many digits are before the decimal.
declarations.title: numOfIntegral

declarations.comments: Counts how many digits are after the decimal.
declarations.title: numOfFractional

declarations.comments: Returns the integer part of a HugeNum.
declarations.title: integerPart

declarations.comments: Returns the closest integer-valued HugeNum less than or equal to the argument.
declarations.title: floor

declarations.comments: Returns the closest integer-valued HugeNum greater than or equal to the argument.
declarations.title: ceil

declarations.comments: Returns the closest integer-valued HugeNum to the argument.
declarations.title: round

declarations.comments: Returns the fractional part of a HugeNum.
declarations.title: fractionalPart

declarations.comments: Creates a nonnegative value with the same magnitude as the argument.
declarations.title: abs

declarations.comments: Flips the sign. While `negate` from the Prelude does the same, this is faster.
declarations.title: neg

declarations.comments: Raise a HugeNum to an integer power.
declarations.title: pow
